REACT PROPS
------------
    -   Props is generally known as "properties" 
    -   props is sharing all state should be parent to child compoent.
         
        Parent and child
        -----------------

            function Home() {                                      ---> Parent Component

                return <div>
                     <h1> Parent Component</h1> 
                    <About />                                      ----> Child Component 
                </div>
            }

            function About() {
                return <div>   
                    <h1> Child Component</h1> 
                </div>
            }


        Props
        ------

            function Home() {

                const [ceoName,setCeoname] = useState('Saravanan')
                const [companyBio,setCompanyBio] = useState("Since 1997 is started this compnay")

                return <div>
                     <h1> Parent Component</h1> 
                    <About 
                        ceoName = {ceoName}
                        companyBio = {companyBio}
                    />  
                </div>
            }

            - While all state should be pass object strcture.
            - Props keyword is invoked that objects.


            function About(props) {

                return <div>   
                    <h1> Child Component</h1> 

                    <div> Company CEO name is   { props.companyBio} </div>
                    <div> Company Bio  { props.companyBio} </div>



                </div>
            }



    In Short-hand - Object destructuring method.
    --------------------------------------------

            function About( {ceoName,companyBio } ) {

                return <div>   
                    <h1> Child Component</h1> 

                    <div> Company CEO name is   { companyBio} </div>
                    <div> Company Bio  { companyBio} </div>

                </div>
            }




